From: dlinder@cse.unl.edu (Daniel Linder)
Subject: Re: X through Dialup
Date: 27 Sep 1993 15:20:15 GMT

tseng@a.cs.okstate.edu (TSENG CHENG YUAN) writes:
>Hi !
>   I already installed SLS 1.03 on my PC.  Can anyone
>   tell me "How can I use X-applications through Dialup"? 
>   "Will that be very slow through 9600 bps line"?
>    Thanks for your helpness!!
  I would get Term 1.07 and (assuming you are hooking up to a UNIX box
with Linux), compile it on both ends.  This will allow you to start up
X on Linux and run X programs off the remote system.  I run at 14.4, and it
is acceptable, anything less would be painful to say the least...

  I believe the source for Term is on sunsite--try compiling it.  It was
not too hard to get compiled here, and runs great!

  Dan




