From: rlerdorf@netcom.com (Rasmus Lerdorf)
Subject: Zero Unix Expo Interest!
Date: Mon, 27 Sep 1993 16:17:39 GMT

Someone in this group mentioned that one way of getting commercial
developers interested in Linux would be to ask these vendours at
Unix Expo for Linux versions of their products.  

Well, I represented a commercial vendour at Unix Expo, and from the
look of recent discussion, a rather interesting one for Linux people.
I was at the Cyclades booth.  Cyclades is an intelligent I/O card
manufacturer.  I also represented Nutec Corp. which is a Unix
software company.  I didn't have a single person stop by the booth
interested in Linux.  Just about every other imaginable Intel-based
Unix was mentioned, including BSD several times.  In fact, BSD had
a booth very close to me.

I think this is one of the reasons that Linux isn't taken extremely
seriously by most companies.  There needs to be higher level interest
before commercial developers will come around.  

